reviews:
Spotless
Newly painted
Comfortable bed but small
Quirky decor
Extremely quiet if room facing inner courtyard

Safe position, above headlight!
Shower in bath, deep step out onto floor no handholds, dangerous
No coffee maker !!
Toothbrush glasses were paper cups !
Ok location during day but feels iffy around dusk
Room high but small floor space,no seats and very difficult to move round if two people share rooms
Toilet has no washing facilities and in different compartment to bathroom
Only 1 USB socket in room so need converters
Breakfast is very limited & expensive for 20€

One of the best hotel experiences we've ever had traveling! The staff at the hotel were incredible from the moment we arrived. Got in very early morning from a flight from the U.S. and while our room wasn't ready they freely offered up the hammam shower to us so we could clean up while waiting for our room. Game changer!
Warm, friendly and helpful. The hotel is quiet and comfortable and had everything we needed.

The Hotel Fabric was excellent. Fabulous location, very comfortable bed, quiet, great shower and the staff were extremely helpful and accommodating. We also enjoyed the honour bar which was available in the lounge/reception area. Thank you so very much for your top service.

The hotel is in my newly favorite neighborhood in Paris. Not super-touristy, full of interesting options for food, wandering, etc.
The hotel has character, isn't like an American chain hotel at all, has great service, and is pretty easy to get to from CDG.

A really loves hotel, with a very supportive staff team who welcomed us, upgraded us but where incredibly supportive during our stay. You felt like you were away from home but at home! Great room, lovely reception area with onto coffee and soft drinks and an honesty bar. Relaxed feel in a great neighbourhood snd incredibly close to the metro. What was there not to like!

This is a really fantastic hotel - the common areas, room itself, breakfast and location (great restaurants/shops nearby) were tremendous. The staff were really professional and helpful. I will definitely come back to stay again.

We stayed 3 nights at Hotel Fabric prior to sailing on a river cruise. Arrived early around 11AM and our rooms were available shortly after that. The rooms are on the smaller size, however our room had enough room for the two of us. There was a lobby and spacious open area for the yummy breakfast and meet ups with others in our group. There is an honor bar available in the evenings, but there is also a grocery store next door. The staff was courteous and helpful, giving suggestions for our dinners around the area. There is a new restaurant across the street with tapas/small plates type of dining as well as a few larger entree's to split. Our group of 9 really enjoyed this. Having said this, if you are looking for a hotel in the center of town - this one probably isn't for you. We had to take a taxi or uber to get more into the tourist areas. However, the "train/underground" is just a few blocks away. If you've got flexibility in your location, this is a great hotel.

Very tentative staff providing excellent service, hotel with a nice ambiance, very good value for money, would definitely stay in this hotel again and can give it our best recommendations (for business or pleasure)

A very beautiful hotel on the perfect street in a vibrant neighborhood of Paris! Staff was extremely helpful and very kind. Well appointed rooms with extremely comfortable beds! Hotel feels brand new. Each night there is a terrific “honesty bar” and every morning an excellent breakfast buffet presented in the lobby. Highly recommend!!!

A warm, welcoming and beautifully appointed hotel.
Lots of great touches to make the stay great - unassuming polite service, tea all day long, large comfortable room and a great breakfast selection.
The leaving gift was a lovely touch.

The Hotel Fabric is my new favorite hotel in Paris, located in a vibrant neighborhood with tons of great restaurants. The staff are always pleasant, accommodating, and informative. The decor is interesting and unique. It feels like home but also serves as a great place to get work done. This is the third or fourth time I've stayed here.

Our home away from home while in Paris. Whoever said that Parisians are not friendly clearly never stayed at the Hotel Fabric. The hospitality and attention to detail of the Hotel Fabric staff was unparalleled. The setting was a delightful balance of chic and comfort. One of the most charming aspects of the hotel was the honesty bar, which gave access for weary travelers to enjoy an evening glass of wine (or other digestif) in a relaxed setting to reset for the next day. The quality of the wine as well as the affordability was such a pleasant surprise, as we were able to sample French wine and local beers that we may not have otherwise experienced; all while our 12 year-old daughter was comfortable up in the room binge watching Emily in Paris while we enjoyed a little solitude😊 Situated just a short walk from the Marais, perhaps the most fashionable district in Paris, the location was an accessible walk to lovely cafés and shopping, but also due to its location on a less busy street perfect for catching an Uber to more distant arrondissements. As a family of three, this room worked well, with both a queen and twin bed, small refrigerator with fresh water daily and a little space for our uneaten goodies from the day. Another aspect that I loved was the digital city guide provided on the website that outlines the local restaurants and exhibits in the neighborhood. I highly recommend the hotel for families and couples alike!

Great stay in Paris. Stayed with family and the family room was great.

Front desk were very helpful throughout the stay and hotel is in great location with good places to eat close by and metro stop close to hotel to access rest of Paris.

Breakfast in hotel is good too

If you ever are fortunate enough to find yourself hosted at the Hotel Fabric, I hope you enjoy your stay as much as I did. My adult daughter and I spent 6 nights at this hotel. It was a warm cozy place to come and go from. The breakfasts were fresh, savory and sweet. Staff were knowledgable, always attentive and respectful of our privacy. The neighborhood is full of delights and the city center easy to access when desired.

Was greeted with a very friendly welcome who spoke fluent English to help check in and answer any questions we had. The hotel was quirky and kept extremely clean. The rooms felt spacious and cleaned regularly. All staff were extremely helpful, giving us great travel tips and recommendations on places to eat and visit within the local area and around Paris. Overall a lovely experience and I will definitely be returning!

Great hotel, full value ++ for the price and many more treats.
We stayed at the hotel (Triple room in the 3rd floor) for 4 nights in March 2023. We really liked the staff (from the reception to the farewell after 5 days), the room is pleasant, clean and well-kept, the location in the 11th qr is very convenient. Very close to 2 metro stations, restaurants and cafes. Hope to come back again soon.

This former industrial boutique hotel has a class and charm about it that I really liked. It's a former textile factory in a trendy neighbourhood, well-linked to the centre of Paris.

I appreciated the small touches in the room paying homage to the history of the property. Bed was comfy, and I liked the long desk so I could get some work done. The breakfast was excellent - and the general ambience of the reception and dining area was classy.

Highly recommended!

Overall this is a fabulous hotel, especially for the price. It's centrally located with many shops and cafes within a short walk. The woman who checked us in was warm and friendly....I wish I could remember her name. Our room was small, but we already knew that. Although small, it was clean and well-decorated with a nice bathroom.

Breakfast in the beautiful lobby was perfect....nothing beats a European breakfast! The fitness center is small--just a few pieces of cardio equipment and dumbbell weights in a small space--but was sufficient for some sweat-inducing cardio and an excellent dumbbell workout.

Next time we're in Paris we'd happily stay here again, although in a larger room.

Beautiful decorated hotel with great staff! We are coming for many years to Paris and it s has been a long time ago that we experienced such a warm and professional welcome in a Parisian hotel: from the coffee offered on arrival, the immediate disposal of our room on arrival at 11.00, the free upgrade of our room, the good advice for the restaurants in the immediate surroundings of the hotel! Merci beaucoup. You are making the difference! The room was very spacious, nicely decorated and very clean. The 11ieme is very nice to discover at a 5 minutes walk of the Marais!

We stayed two nights in Hotel Fabric. Having read the positive reviews I was confident that it was a good choice. However, my expectations were exceeded from the moment we walked in and were warmly greeted at check in. Hotel Fabric was exceptional - mainly because of its wonderful staff. The amenities were perfect, everything was clean and comfortable. The staff were incredibly helpful. I know that I would most certainly chose to come back here when I am next in Paris and would welcome it to anyone coming to Paris.
The location was ideal and convenient too. Cafes, metros and bakeries were a short distance away - and a supermarket just next door.
Thank you for making our stay so delightful!

I have stayed at Hotel Fabric three times (the last being January 2023) and will be there next month for a fourth visit. It is always a pleasure arriving there on rue de la Folie Mericourt. The staff is awesome, welcoming, fun and super knowledgeable. I love the 24/7 service. The rooms are very comfortable, clean and well equipped, as is the hotel. The lobby area is super decontracte (relaxed) with a great vibe. The location could not be better. You walk out the door and you have Cafe Mericourt (the best coffee, cutest friendliest staff and the best food (only open until 3). Gotta go. Croyez-moi. The newest addition a few doors down, Chambre Noir Cave Paris wine bar. Don't miss a visit here. And a new great hamburger place. The name escapes me, but the owner was so cool and we needed a good burger and fries. Hit the spot! I owe him a Texas gift upon return. Place de la Republique, le Marais, Canal St. Martin all within short fabulous walking distance. In any direction, the walk is interesting and there is so much to discover wherever you are going. Up to our departure at 5:30 am on the first day of the strike we had the best Taxi driver that drives regularly for Hotel Fabric. There is a small gym and it's all you need, if you need it. This last time I was with my best friend (girl friend) and we stayed 9 nights ! Could not have been better. I will always be back. Good habits are hard to break. Bonnes sejours et profitez-vous.

First off, the staff is excellent - very friendly, welcoming and extremely helpful when needed.

This lovely hotel was precisely what we were seeking: CLEAN, QUIET, STYLISH, within a NON-TOURISTY area, yet close to many other beautiful areas in Paris. Also...to have that beautiful lounge area open 24/7 is an element that we enjoyed VERY much. The sauna was great, too.

We LOVED our stay there and we'll definitely be staying at Hôtel Fabric when we visit again.

THANK YOU for a wonderful stay there.

I really loved the decor and interior design.
Really appreciated having the lobby available for our usage, super cozy. Breakfast is very generous. Location is good as well, walking distance from a nice coffee shop and pharmacy nearby, right by a supermarket and close to several restaurants.

If I were to give one small recommendation, it would be to have better coffee.

The hotel is beautifully decorated with large spacious rooms. The hotel is 3 minutes from the tube and is within 20mins of the Champs Elysees and have lots of restaurants and cafes nearby.

The breakfast had a lot of variety from cereal to croissants and coffee.

Super friendly and helpful team at Hotel Fabric. Three of us stayed 2 nights in their deluxe double room. It had the most comfortable (single) sofa bed I've come across! The room was a bit warm, so even with the cold spell in Paris at the time, we turned off the heat and left the window ajar during the night. Good selection at breakfast - don't miss the two warm items tucked away on a table in a corner. Honesty bar great for a nightcap before heading to back to the room. Location is great - felt safe walking around in the evening, two metro stops within 5min walk, one of which (5) has goes directly to Gare du Nord. Plenty of bakeries, patisseries and restaurants nearby.

Very nice cosy hotel on a quiet street just across some busy avenues. Nice atmosphere, gentle staff, spacious room and very good breakfast. Good price for quality. Well located near 4 metro stations which can lead to any place in the city. Recommend!

A great, comfortable, clean hotel with incredibly friendly and knowledgeable staff who went above and beyond to help with some of our planning by making some great recommendations. Convenient to Metro lines and some great restaurants and bakeries. Would stay again and highly recommend to others.

A short weekend out, winter days in Paris and the hotel proved to be the excellent choice: a very nice room, well-designed, great bathroom, … but also the lobby, breakfast area are are well designed and maintained. Breakfast was excellent. On the list for a next trip to Paris because also the quarter is very nice

Upon my early arrival from the airport, I received an extremely warm welcome from the staff and enjoyed tea and madeleines in the cozy lobby while waiting for the room to be ready. The room was immaculate, attractive, and well appointed, and very quiet. The hammam was a particular treat. The breakfast in the lobby was outstanding.

We spent a whole week at this hotel and were very satisfied. We booked 4 rooms for a party of 7 people: 4 adults and 3 kids. The staff was very friendly and forthcoming. The rooms are nice & very clean, the nights are quiet and you can have a good rest, even when facing the street!
Metro Station is a 3 mins walk. The area has a lot of restaurants to offer with Canal St. Martin and Place de la Republique in close walking distance. We can absolutely recommend this place.

This hotel was great in every way. The decor is modern and cosy & has everything you need with a modern bathroom. The rooms are a good size for a big city too. All the staff are so friendly and helpful, and there’s a really chilled atmosphere in the lobby with plenty of seats & an honesty bar for alcohol with free tea, coffee, water & snacks. It’s in a trendy part of town and easily accessible to several metro stations. Thanks Hotel Fabric for an awesome stay!

Helpful and friendly employees. Nicely decorated and comfortabel rooms and industrial decoration of the hotel. Central location, metro and parking garage in the immediate vicinity. Close by Palace de la Bastille. All principale sightseeing of Paris reachable within 30 minutes. Nice neighborhood, with several restaurants and cafés. Fine breakfest

We spent 3 nights at Hotel Fabric in December. We had two rooms (in a connecting corridor) for our party of 3 adults and 2 young children. The stay was perfect! The room was extremely clean, beautifully decorated and well equipped. The lobby was gorgeous and we appreciated the all day cappuccino machine and snacks that were available. The breakfast exceeded expectations with fresh squeezed juices and a large variety of foods. We also enjoyed the beautiful and relaxing hassam spa. The location is very convenient to two different metro stations and was in walking distance to a lot of restaurants. But the most impressive part of this hotel was the customer service and their attention to detail. They were incredibly patient and friendly as we asked for directions and suggestions on food. When my 6 year old spilled hot chocolate everywhere and I was horrified the concierge didn’t miss a beat and was so very kind.
This quiet, unique hotel made our trip to Paris absolutely perfect. I would go back again and again!

Wonderful comfortable clean friendly hotel, and we love the location, too! We had no complaints and highly recommend this place. Lovely staff, great vibe, good breakfast, all good! We've stayed twice and will do it again!

Stay here- lovely hotel, great breakfast, has a small fitness center and a spa/steam room for guests (included). Three nearby metros, roughly 4-7 min walks depending which line and your walking pace.

I wrote a more detailed account but TA deleted it when I went to add photos🤦🏼‍♀️ I’m taking the time to re-write a shorter review though as I really loved the hotel and would stay here again in a heartbeat. The location is excellent and also, quite quiet. Staff is friendly and unobtrusive. Beautiful lobby, very comfortable and spacious rooms (space is subjective, but consider where you are and what is typical for that city).

Super hotel in a great neighbourhood. Large rooms, comfy bed. Very good breakfast, nice communal area with tea & coffee. Loved the steam room. Very friendly helpful staff will definitely return. We ate at the restaurant opposite L’insolite .. absolutely delicious would recommend

Hotel was great, the team were welcoming and keen to make difference to our stay.
Room was clean, comfortable, not as large as perhaps I thought it would be, but certainly not small, and for the amount of time we spent there it was more than adequate.
Complimentary coffee 24/7 and a lovely lounge feel area with honesty bar in the evening.

We've stayed in Hotel Fabric for only 1 night, but it was perfect! The room was big and the hotel offers so much. You can also access the gym 😎 Loved the opend bar for coffee and tea during the day, and the fact that we could leave our bags on the reception even after our check-out. I would recommend you to stay here, the hotel has a great access to the metro too.

Third time we stayed in this hotel. What makes this hotel special:
-Excellent breakfast.
-Very good connections with Metro to all parts of Paris.
-We were allowed to check out one hour later.
-Very friendly personnel.

Great location, staff were very friendly and informative. They even helped book a show that we were struggling to get tickets for , 5 star service.

Bed was very comfortable 😀 I would definitely recommend staying here for you trip to Paris

We are repeat guests - stayed previously for one week in 2018, twice this time around (3 nights at the start of our tip and 5 nights at the end) and would be happy to return in the future.

Located in the 11th arrondissement – it is a very trendy location (described over several years now as up-and-coming) and is much more local than touristy. Not an upscale neighborhood and not within view of major attractions, instead a groovy, local/artisanal neighbourhood with many excellent restaurants and from which we loved walking, everywhere (including to the nearby Canal St Martin and Le Marais (15 minutes) as well as to further destinations like the Louvre (40 minutes) and Operas Garnier (45 minutes)). The Metro is nearby (5 minutes) if you prefer to ride.

Small scale with just 33 rooms, the Hotel Fabric blends an industrial feel (staying true to its 19th century roots as a former textile factory) with modern design. The lobby/breakfast room is large and gorgeous. While the stairwells and corridors to the rooms are dark, they open into bright, colourful rooms with huge windows and high ceilings.

3-night stay (at start of our trip) – Superior Triple room:
Booked a Superior Double room and were upgraded to a Superior Triple room (21 m2) with courtyard view on our arrival, nice but ... was wanting for the street view of the superior double that we booked.
Enjoyed the in-room day bed this room offers as it provided a place to spread out a bit more, to open our luggage. Did not love the toilet being separate from the sink/tub/shower.

5-night stay (at end of our trip) – Deluxe room:
Booked a Deluxe room (24 m2) with courtyard view. Enjoyed the extra space this room offers. However, did not love the dual wardrobes/closet space butting up against both sides of the bed (would much prefer a nightstand for a spot to place hand cream, book, phone, wine glass, etc.).

Comparison to our 7-night stay in 2018 – Superior Double room:
Stayed in a Superior Double room (20 m2) with street facing view. This was our favourite room of the 3 room categories we have tried – by far. Preferred layout and as well as having the street view this room category offers (instead of the courtyard views which left us feeling somewhat exposed to adjacent neighbors).

Opportunities for improvement:
• Upgraded hair dryers (to replace the current ones, which are the worst we have used, ever) would be a simple action that would surely be appreciated by all guests. (There is no on/off button, must hold down a button to keep it running, and it runs extremely weakly at that).
• In-room Nespresso (or any kind of coffee) maker would be much appreciated.
• The Shower (Deluxe room) was not well sealed, so the floor was a big puddle after a shower.
• A proper cappuccino (barista-style coffee) at breakfast would be a nice offering – not only adding a personal touch to breakfast, but a better coffee than that which the available push-button machine made - a cappuccino that tasted like hot chocolate, no thank you!
• Replenishing of water in the room was inconsistent.
• Number of towels in the room was inconsistent (one day we were left with only one bath towel for the two of us).
• Amenities – fewer bathroom amenities provided than in 2018 (this time around – no body lotion, no make up remover wipes, no hand cream – all provided on our first visit).
• Advance contact from the hotel to inform on use of the new Navigo cards (since so many people use the Metro and since the Metro is transitioning away from the printed carnets to this electronic card) would be of immense value. Specifically, tips on purchasing and how to get your photo onto it would be helpful. Assistance acquiring/purchasing in advance (perhaps having ready at check-in) would be next level.

Room tips:
• Some rooms have baths with showers (with an uncomfortably big step in/out) while others have walk-in rain showers (our preference). The superior triple had the tub/shower combo which we didn’t love.
• Some rooms come with a separate toilet (other side of the room than the sink/tub/shower) – this was the case in the superior triple room we had and did not enjoy this. Not sure if the room type dictates this or not – recommend asking when you book.
• Some rooms are street-facing while others offer a courtyard view – rooms on the courtyard side are quieter.
• Although quieter, rooms with a courtyard view feel less private – our corner room was adjacent to another room (hotel or residential, not sure) and also across from a residence. With the curtains and windows open (letting in the natural light and fresh air), we felt quite exposed – from the bed we could see people in the window just an arms-length or so away.
• The courtyard view – looking down you see this courtyard is the place for the building’s garbage and recycling bins (not park-like).

A few recommendations:
• Opera Garnier – after hours Mystery Tour guided visit (book online in advance)
• L’acolyte de L’onsolite for dinner – just down the street
• Utopie for pastries – 6-minute walk
• Alain Ducasse for chocolate – 15-minute walk
• Pierre Herme for macarons – several locations, one just a 12-minute walk

Travel tip:
1. The metro is transitioning away from printed tickets/carnets to an electronic Navigo card.
o If you purchase a Navigo card, be sure to purchase one for each person. Despite being told at the ticket counter that one card can be shared between the two of us, and therefore sold just one card – it was more than a bit frustrating when we tried to use it only to learn it didn’t work.
o If you buy the Navigo card, be sure to check the dates for which it is valid. We waited in a long, slow line to make our purchase and then immediately proceeded to use the card only to discover it did not work – why? Because the person at the ticket counter made it active beginning the next day. OMG so frustrating.
o The card requires you add your photo onto the card for it to be legally usable – but how do you do that? Recommend researching this before you travel.
2. Waterproof runners for those rainy days!

Hotel was as good as eight years ago when we previously stayed. The reception team are so helpful, welcoming and friendly . Whilst the rooms and bathroom are typically Paris size they have everything you need plus huge industrial size windows with beautiful curtains . The rain shower worked a treat and the breakfast is both generous in selection and also in availability particularly good when you are on holiday and don’t wish to rise at 8am. In summary a really good find and the area is perfect with some very good restaurants within a short walk but also everyday style places. A gem

I highly recommend this hotel. The staff are very friendly. I will definitely stay at Fabric next time I visit Paris. The staff spoke english very fluently & were very helpful & responsive in every single request I had.

Great price point for Paris. Stylish place, very helpful and friendly staff, nice room and bathroom. Not huge but has everything you need. Quality bed, and bathroom has Occitane amenities. Good breakfast - included with our room rate. Overall great stay and would/will stay again.

I very highly recommend staying at this hotel and we will book again on our next trip to Paris. The English speaking staff are friendly and professional and knowledgeable. The Hotel prints a list of what's on, recommended restaurants (and how long it takes to walk there!), has 24 hr coffee (a machine that offers everything - I mean everything; expresso, cappuccino, etc) and a nice breakfast to start the day. The beds are very comfortable - a must for me and my back, which did not ache at all, and a lovely shower. Sparkling clean rooms, sparkling clean hotel. Every day there were two fresh bottle of both still and sparking water. My husband had to do some work here and there, and the desk was spacious enough with loads of plugs (the room has lots of outlets) and it's quiet at night. Quiet from outside noise and unlike most hotels we've stayed in, did not hear a peep from another room. The bathroom had enough room for our toiletry kits and any overflow just went right into the open shelving outside the bathroom. Lovely toiletries provided (l'Occitane) and thank you for a shower cap!!! Plenty of towels. Nice maids (you should tip daily, folks) and really the only thing was just one rest for a suitcase and we had two. But no matter! It fits by the door, or under the desk, I'm in my sixties and had no issue bending down to use my suitcase, but I could have unloaded everything into the shelving so my choice.
We stayed four days and found the location convenient for walking, bus, metro.Loads of restaurants and if you don't go to F.IE.F. across the street, you are missing an astonishing meal. There was an advisement in the lift for guests to book a taxi early due to travel issues so we took them at their word and had no problem scheduling a cab for 6:30 a.m. The decor is so stylish, but not uncomfortable at all. There is an honor bar, an assortment of books to leaf through and we loved this: returning at 12:00ish or so you ring the night bell. We are in our 60s, not a criminal looking couple :) but the night concierge asked for our room. That's security folks, he didn't assume our age made us OK to just walk into the hotel. Although we do prefer the lower arrondissements, we can spend the day there and return to Fabric for a nightcap and a great night's sleep.P.S. I have seen this written up as a hotel for hipsters but the week we spent it was all families, with a few solo travelers and couples. Hip looking yes but not hipster central.

We stayed in the top floor room on the 4th floor which has a staircase in the room up to a double bed on the mezzanine as well as two single beds in the main room. The bathroom was large. It was perfect for us and our two boys and would work for a group of four friends too.

The hotel is in a great location with two metro stations close by and it is easy to walk to some attractions etc. The area is full of lovely cafes and restaurants too and they don’t feel as touristy.

The hotel reception team are fantastic and before our visit had helped out with advice about getting to Disneyland and a PSG match. It is definitely worth asking the hotel to book any taxis in advance too and the company they use are excellent. We used them to get to Disney and back which was lucky as there was a train strike on the day.

The hotel also sent us a list of restaurants they recommended before we visited at my request which was really useful.

We opted for hotel breakfast which was fine but you could easily find somewhere to eat close by for breakfast. There is an honesty bar in the evening and free hot drinks are available all day - the kids loved getting themselves a hot chocolate each night.

This was our second stay at Hotel Fabric and I would definitely recommend it to anyone visiting Paris.

Fabulous hotel worth every penny. Large rooms and very helpful attentive staff. Relaxed feel and great location especially for the young. Didn't have breakfast as lots of local coffee shops ad bakeries but an honestly bar in the evenings and complimentary water, teas, coffees etc.

Nicely located, quiet streets and with short distance to SUBway and buses. We were welcomed by the reseptionist who helped us with any questions we had. The rooms is nicely refurbished and equiwipped well. The general service troughout the 3 day stay was good. The cleaning of rooms good, but was missing the last touch by cleaning the walls and joints in the shower.

Really nice little hotel located on a cool street in a nice neighborhood with lots of bars, restaurants & odd stores (a store with only puzzles!)

Staff is really serviceminded and Claire is the star!

We just finished a wonderful 4-night stay at Hotel Fabric last week. From the check-in experience to the room finishing, I cannot recommend this little gem enough. Firstly, it's location is wonderful if you're looking to explore a (slightly) quieter side of Paris. Oberkampf is an up and coming neighborhood full of awesome restaurants and shops and easily connects to Marais for nightlife, bars, etc. The hotel itself is situated on a side street away from the main boulevard so road noise is not as big of an issue.

The hotel rooms are small but wonderfully appointed. The desk area provides plenty of room for laying out belongs or getting some emails done. My only small gripe with the design of the rooms is that there is not very much counter space in the bathroom - so finding a place for Toiletries for more than two persons can be tight. I also really appreciated the complimentary sparkling and still bottles of water nightly in the room.

What makes Hotel Fabric really shine is the staff. Everyone was so pleasant and accommodating. The desk staff was very helpful in planning out dinner reservations for us. All in all, a wonderful stay at Hotel Fabric.

We thoroughly enjoyed our stay at the Hotel Fabric. The service was exceptional. When we checked in around noon, our room was not yet available. The woman checking us in was quick and pleasant and let us know that our luggage would be delivered to our room as soon as it was available. She then gave us a great lunch recommendation. When we got into our room, our luggage was there and set up on the luggage stands. Breakfast service was equally as good. When we checked out the gentleman at the front desk helped us out with our luggage. (Once again, we had stored our bags for the day.) Everyone at desk was pleasant and acknowledged you with a friendly hello. Sometimes, it is just the small things that make a stay great.

We booked a Deluxe Room at the hotel and had plenty of room, particularly by European standards. Bathroom was well equipped. The only thing we would suggest is that they add a coffee table in front of the sofa in the room. The room and the hotel was a great value. Decor in the lobby is good.

Overall, I would say the location is okay. The hotel is on a quiet street with local shops and restaurants nearby. It is a bit of a walk to the main tourist attractions in Paris. There is a great local street market that was going on in the park along the Bd Richard-Lenoir on Sunday.

We would absolutely stay there again.

I spent just under a week with my elderly mother at this fabulous hotel. The location is simply brilliant - a calm base to return to after a day's exploring and night's eating at so many wonderful local restaurants. You can walk to so many interesting areas from this hotel (particularly the Marais), including of course the wonderful 11th arrondissement in which the hotel resides. I cannot stress enough how kind and courteous the staff are. No challenge to difficult. No ask a problem. The rooms are luxurious and the triple glazing means a peaceful night's sleep. We hope to return!

Well appointed hotel in a great part of Paris with strong transport links. Rooms were big (for Paris) and new. Staff were incredibly helpful, providing great restaurant tips. We would certainly stay again.

We try to get away for a short break at least every month and have tried many hotels . In short ; this is the best hotel we have found .

It’s is superbly located on a quite street walking distance to all you will need . It has two very handy Metro stations if you don’t fancy walking .

We had a superior room overlooking the street . Being on the street side was not adversely affected by noise - it’s a quiet one way street .

The room is so relaxing , comfortable and has all you need . The shower was massive ! Loads of mirrors in the room and bathroom for dressing up for a night out . They have really thought the decor through to make sure the room works , as well as being relaxing .

The foyer is a nice and usable chill out area . Coffee on tap ! And Just the sort of breakfast you’d want in Paris . The honesty bar is a nice touch . I also liked the art (I’m a reader of George Orwell !) .

Above all , the asset this hotel has (in addition to the above ) are its staff . Warm and welcoming and go out of their way to help . We tried some of the restaurant recommendations and they were much better to those offered in our Lonely Planet guide !

A few other nice things :

- the coffee and bottled water whenever you need it is great .
- there is a small supermarket next door
- the area is rich with good food and bars that are not over frequented by tourists.

Overall . For us , the perfect stay . (Check out our other reviews as you will see that we don’t often write that !)

A great hotel full of individuality and a pleasant change from standard hotels. Staff were extremely helpful and full of great recommendations for the surrounding area. Excellent continental breakfast

Good location 20 minute walk to the River Seine where we took the river bus to explore the main sights.

A great two night stay, would have stayed longer but hotel was fully booked

Friendly, clean, big nice rooms with comfy beds. The brekfast was fresh.
Quiet area, nice lunch and dinner restaurants across the street.
Walking distance to Marais and Metro nearby.
A really nice stay:)
We will be back!

Had a great stay at Hotel Fabric. The location of the hotel suited us really well. It’s 5 mins walk from the metro, in a really nice area. Lots of great bars and restaurants nearby too.

The staff were very helpful, rooms were spotless, stylish, and very comfortable. The breakfast deserves a mention too, very good indeed.

Hope to return soon.

This hotel was excellent! The staff was welcoming and helpful and went out their way to ensure you had a great stay. The location was excellent and within walking distance of most things. It is surrounded by great little shops and restaurants.

My husband and I had a wonderful experience at Hotel Fabric. We just stayed 1 night and wish we were there longer! We received a courtesy upgrade to an amazing room. Everything was top class, right from the décor, hygiene, and comforts. The neighborhood is great and very connected by public transport. The staff were extremely hospitable. Would stay there again in a heartbeat!

Our stay was faultless. We were lucky to be upgraded to a larger room and it was fantastic - clean, quiet, good air con, good WiFi, good shower!!! Receptionists were welcoming, informative and helpful. We didn’t take breakfast in the hotel choosing to use local cafes that were superb and plentiful. No hotel bar but honesty bar in a very relaxed and comfortable reception area that was a great idea!!! Will definitely consider staying here again next time we are in Paris.

We stayed at Hotel Fabric for 3 hot August nights to celebrate a birthday. The reception team were so welcoming and helpful and the room was larger than we hoped for in Paris with high windows that allowed us to get fresh air without lots of noise at the front of the hotel.
We loved the bathroom with waterfall shower and L’Occitane products.

Breakfast was great; good choice of pastries, cheeses, hams and eggs. Great coffee and being able to get a drink (and madeleine) during the day was nice.

A lovely touch was the vouchers for the honesty bar and the gift on our final day. Wouldn’t hesitate to stay there again as the ambience is restful and with metro lines very near and a short walk to the Marais and gods neighbourhood bars and restaurants.

Great location in a quiet part of Paris. Rooms are cool and amazing lobby with comfortable lounging chairs, great location and priced well ... would definitely stay again. Amazing check in staff and great friendly place

Hotel Fabric is located in a neat little neighborhood in the 11th district. This was our second stay and we would book there again. The building was an old textile factory and maintains the old hard wood floors and brick walls. The breakfast is everything you could want, fresh croissants, chocolate croissants, eggs, cold cuts, cheese, but the star is the coffee machine. It will make your heart's desire.
The hotel is an easy walk to two metro stations, restaurants are around the corner, down the street, and the variety - traditional French food, pizza, Greek, and combinations. An excellent bakery is a block away, get sandwiches for a picnic, and great pastries.
Grocery store next door and several pharmacies near. Everyone - the hotel staff, the wait staff, everyone is so nice. We did not encounter a single rude Parisian, even at the airport!

It was incredible! The rooms and hotel itself is really clean and well taken care of. The staff is wonderfull, you can get tea, coffee en water for free and even take it to go! We will visit again, it was dreamy!

Excellent customer service by helpful,friendly staff in a great location. Good breakfast that was included in the deal. Very comfortable room that was well designed. Everything needed for a great city break.

This is the second time this year we have stayed at hôtel Fabric. This time it was with our daughter. The room we were given was perfect to allow privacy and had excellent air conditioning which was very much appreciated in the 35 degree heat!

The staff are always professional and friendly. They also gave excellent restaurant recommendations and guidance with our stay in Paris.

We will certainly be returning here whenever we are next in Paris. It’s a quiet street but a métro ride away from all the ‘big’ tourist attractions.

Breakfast was varied and tasty. The honesty bar is a real extra for those that cannot go out on the town with children and I cannot recommend this place enough.

Merci bien! À bientôt…

Fantastic staff, facilities, room and location - will definitely book again when staying in Paris! Free coffee/hot chocolate all day, small but clean gym and very friendly and helpful staff. walking distance to metro and has a grocery store next door

A fabulous hotel, well placed. Nice area. Great spacious room with comfy beds for us and still room for our daughters bed. Breakfast is a buffet, plenty of choices. Honesty bar in the evening in the spacious lobby/lounge area. Friendly staff.

Friendly staff, well designed space. Our double room was a little on the small side but the triple room my kids had was huge!
Only criticism - hairdryer not great and toiletries were not refilled.
Loved the hamman.
Breakfast was okay - croissants could have been better!
However there were some really nice touches - such as the welcome drink, all day coffee and water and small leaving gift.
Would definitely stay again! Hotel was quiet and beds super comfy in a fantastic location.

I was unfamiliar with the 11th but had to stay there for a class. This hotel was fantastic! The lobby was cozy, the breakfast abundant, and I loved the all-day coffee machine and happy hour honor bar. The room was enormous and updated, with blackout curtains and a luxurious spa-like bathroom. The little touches like a welcome note with drink coupons and a thank you gift on my last night really added to the personal service. The front desk staff was so helpful and friendly. It is not near most typical tourist attractions in Paris, but as a result the nearby cafes are much more authentic and affordable. There are some cool artisan shops and galleries in the area as well.

There is so much to recommend about Hotel Fabric, it's hard to know where to start. Charming and beautiful, perfectly maintained, beautifully designed, and the staff could not be more professional, friendly, and accommodating. Monika and Lea are amazing, but really the entire staff was incredibly sweet and the service was above and beyond.

I had originally booked a fancy place near the Opera house but after reading all the reviews of this place, I took a gamble. This was a big birthday trip angled around eating and wine. I LOVED THIS PLACE! This is a perfect little boutique hotel in Paris. Since we were staying 6 nights, they gave us a free upgrade to a 'bigger' room. Granted, the room wasn't huge, but it's Paris and no hotel rooms are. The bed was big and comfortable, the AC worked very well, the shower was HEAVEN and the staff were incredibly friendly and kind. Would 100% stay again and recommend to anyone going to Paris.

ALSO - this neighborhood is so cute and chill. There are fantastic little restaurants and wine bars all around. Right across the street we stumbled into a brand new restaurant and had some of the best wine (and chocolate mousse) of our trip, wound up befriending the owner and buying 4 bottles from her. We walked everywhere, there's a metro right at the corner and the honor bar was a charming touch for a little drink before bed. We opted out of the breakfast because there are so many fantastic bakeries nearby, but the free coffee bar was a major win every morning.

10/10 - amazing price for what you get.

We stayed here during a short family trip in July. The staff was very friendly and capable to help in French and English - e.g. with restaurant recommendations. Rooms are modern, stylish and clean. Breakfast buffet was ample and elegant.

The location is excellent. Metro station(s) are nearby as are grocery stores, laundromat and many good restaurants. Also, there is a direct metro line to Gare du Nord and from there you can get on the train to CDG.

Overall, I can only recommend this hotel and during my/our next stay to Paris I will stay there again - for sure.

We've stayed here now 4 times. Great, quiet location in 11th easy walking distance to Marais and Seine. Great Metro access. Hotel itself is very well maintained, nice, clean and modern bathrooms, and very comfortable beds. Good air conditioning. Staff are very helpful and polite. Highly recommend.

We stayed for four nights after having to cancel our trip due to Covid twice. We arrived well before book in time but they had our room ready and had upgraded us which was a real delight. staff were attentive and very helpful. The room was very clean and the bath was huge. Breakfast was a lovely mix and something to please everyone. Coffee and tea was always available in the foyer. Close to the metro and very central.
Would return and very happy to recommend

I can't say enough good things about this hotel, with generous rooms in an outstanding location. The service went above and beyond -- we had a lot of extra requests and questions: laundry, adding a night, then having to subtract a night and they were kind and helpful every time. Breakfast was delicious!

We stayed for 4 nights and it was so amazing! The staff were incredibly friendly. The location is really great-near metro stations and some nice places to eat. We really enjoyed the spa experience and also the free tea in the lobby.
We would thoroughly recommend this hotel!

We had a lovely stay at the Hotel Fabric. It is in the trendy 11th. Lots of great wine bars, restaurants and cafés nearby. The hotel is very quiet. The staff is amazing.
Book a breakfast included room as the breakfast is delicious.
There is a free espresso machine in the lobby all day and honor bar from 6:00 pm on. Our deluxe room was nice. Everything is clean. I highly recommend.

Very nice rooms, and a perfect service.
The manager and team are remarkable.
The breakfast is rich and very tasty and the location is great, close to several metro stations. A few restaurants and bars are located just near the hotel. Very recommended.

A beautiful gem of a hotel in the 11th arrondissement, Hotel Fabric is gracious, spotlessly clean, elegant and unique. Every member of the staff was welcoming, friendly, and extremely helpful. When I needed to extend my stay they made it very easy to the best of their capacity. I will definitely be back.

We stayed two nights and found the hotel staff friendly and helpful. Rooms were clean and tastefully decorated. Loved the "honesty bar" system and found the location of the hotel to be perfect - surrounded by vibrant wine bars and restaurants. It made us feel like we were staying in an area popular with locals, not just tourists, which we prefer.

We stayed for a week. Very nice and clean rooms. Always water in the fridge. Breakfast is good. Very service minded staff at the reception who is ready with sightseeing tips and tips for local restaurants. Small street with good bars, but can be a bit noisy if your room is facing the street.
Don’t miss Fief - the one star Michelin restaurant 100 meters away

Hotel Fabric was incredible. The hospitality was a standout and the amenities made for a very relaxing stay. The hotel is surrounded by incredible restaurants and bars. The culture and atmosphere of the area made the hotel extra special. The Metro service is around the corner providing very easy travel around the city. I highly recommend booking for anyone traveling to Paris.

We stayed at Hotel Fabric for 2 nights and it was perfect! The staff were incredibly friendly and nothing was too much trouble. We really enjoyed the spa experience and also the free tea/coffee etc in the lobby. The room was a great size, very clean and had everything you need for your stay.
The location is really great-near metro stations and some nice places to eat. It also has a shop right next door.
We would thoroughly recommend this hotel and would be keen to return!

I can’t get over how beautiful this hotel is. Very accommodating, staff is very friendly. They have coffee always available, which in a world where Hotels nickel and dime you, this was very refreshing. The focus is on the guest here. Highly recommended.

We had a lovely stay at Hotel Fabric, it is a small intimate hotel, the room was clean and well appointed and the staff were friendly and helpful, we would definitely stay again. The breakfast was also very good!

Would definitely recommend Hotel Fabric, with or without a baby. Originally booked for 2020 without a baby we thought we'd still try it out with a baby 2 years later and so glad we did. Loved the area, definitely gives a sense of Paris culture and not too busy or touristy. Hotel was great, room was clean, good size, enough space for a baby cot and all our stuff! Lovely little extras in the room and hotel too. Breakfast was lovely, highchair available too. The whole atmosphere was very relaxed and the staff couldn't do enough to accommodate us and our baby. Super friendly and some great recommendations. We will be back!

Hotel Fabric was strongly recommended to us and we arrived with high expectations, late June 2022. Nevertheless: our family stay (4 people, 4 nights, two rooms) exceeded all our anticipations!! The atmosphere, the fantastic staff members, the rooms and the gym, the fresh and delicious breakfast, refreshments available all day and night...everything gave us a warm and welcoming feeling! And the interior: beautiful, elaborate, creative...we enjoyed it all with great pleasure, especially the lamps and the beautiful fabrics in the curtains! All areas were always clean and continuously cared for. On top of all this: the location is great! Le Marais is now our top choice in Paris, pleasant area, and easy to go (we often chose walking) to our other places of interest. We give our uppermost recommendations: this hotel is just great!

I can highly recommend Hotel Fabric! We stayed for 4 days mid June 2022. Each and every staff member was friendly, knowledgeable, and willing to help us in any way they could!

The accommodations were spotless and well appointed. The rooms were on the small side, but that did not matter because the hotel lobby was so welcoming with the complimentary coffee/tea/water station to the evening honor bar. We found ourselves happily and comfortably hanging out there.

The neighborhood has some great little restaurants and is great for foodies, and mixed in with the boulangerie, patisserie, & green grocers are some really great boutiques. We only wish we took advantage of the complimentary hamam and gym... but we were too busy exploring the city!

We stayed at hotel fabric for family vacation. Hotel staff is super friendly. Our baggage was delayed and staff really helped us while we navigate through this issue with Air line. They called delivery company on our behalf while we were out. Even after we left, they coordinated with us for missing bags. In summary the best service and staff experience I ever had.

Thank you, hotel fabric for comfortable stay and support. Their breakfast was great and gals that we added in our stay. This will be my go forward hotel for future stays in Paris.

Absolutely amazing stay could not have been any better wonderful staff, wonderful room. Amazing steam room. Breakfast was lovely fresh bread pastries yoghurt meat and cheeses as well as eggs. Really amazing location with lots of good eateries very close by. Staff were absolutely amazing and it really was the most amazing 3 night stay. THANKYOU.

My sister and I stayed here for 4 days after a Mediterranean cruise. It was the perfect end to a fabulous vacation. The hotel is a "boutique hotel" - I think 33 rooms. We loved that. Felt like staying with friends. Great breakfast. We decided we were only doing things in the 11th arrondissement which is where the hotel is located. Great sites to see; great shopping and great restaurants. Everyone on the staff is super nice and helpful. Highly recommended!

we had a wonderful vacation in Hotel Fabric Paris, the hotel is great, the staff members are very friendly and the location and the neighborhood are very nice.
we will defiantly come back to hotel Fabric in our future visits in Paris

Great location. Super clean, very attentive staff. Only 5 minute walk to the metro. All major Paris attractions are about 15-25 minutes from the hotel ( by Metro mostly and few mins walk ). Nice buffet breakfast in the morning. No restaurant onsite but many bistros and cafes within 2 min walk. Small super market right next door also very handy. Would stay here again.

Only a few stops on Metro direct line from Gare du Nord. We stayed over a long weekend, three nights, the staff were very helpful and polite, the breakfasts were plentiful with lots of options. Our street-side double/superior room was very comfortable with brightly coloured fabrics - would stay there again.

This was our first visit to Paris in decades and the first international trip since the start of the pandemic. We had trouble finding a hotel with availability for our entire 10 night stay. We feel very lucky to have happened upon the Hotel Fabric’s description in Fodors. The place was ideal: clean, quiet rooms, helpful staff, great location, solid breakfast…one of us even used the steam room in the basement and got a massage. We loved this place.

Room was very clean and comfortable , personnel very Kind and preoared to answer any question and solve any problem . Fantastic hotel , I Highly recommend it . Also perfect the position close to the metro station

We very much enjoyed our stay at Hotel Fabric. The room and common areas are comfortable and attractive. The staff was uniformly friendly and helpful. The location is a bit off the main tourist circuit but it’s an appealing neighborhood and a short walk to many interesting destinations. We would definitely stay at the hotel again.

Love this hotel. Lovely accommodations and the staff and service is top notch! Cannot recommend enough
The staff does everything to accommodate guests. I found it a great value. Nice lobby to drink coffee available all day.

This is my second stay at this hotel, this time 5 nights with family of 4, including 2 kids. Very modern and clean, comfortable beds for all 4, nice bathroom. We got a very good sleep. The breakfast is excellent, very fresh and it had all the things the kids and I like. The lady organizing the breakfast, Gabriela, is very friendly, extremely helpful and attentive with all the guests. We love the relaxed atmosphere in this hotel; it will always be my first choice when coming to Paris.
